history.content:
Engineering Student Services is hosting a Summer Plans Workshop on Monday, February 12, 6:30-8pm, 240 Bechtel. The event is designed to inspire students to start thinking about their summer plans and to provide them information about summer sessions, research, study abroad, and internships. The workshop is presented by ESS Peer Advisers (including two majoring in EECS) who will share their own experiences. Pizza will be provided!

Facebook event here: https://www.facebook.com/events/2076987165867900/

RSVP here: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfEqmQS4hdgLltQ-sohTkaT5Rod1B3ZSFgH9XEGNVxo59bfYQ/viewform?usp=sf_link
